Cell.Text: [S] Are you sure? | Oh no! They've found me? I need your help! | Please, come with me. I need to speak to you privately.
The who? I'm sorry, I have no idea what you're talking about.

Node.Caption: MS08SaadiaST10BranchTopic: Did you know some Alik'r warriors are looking for a Redguard woman?

Cell.Text: [S] They're mercenaries, only in it for the money. They're led by a man named Kematu. Get rid of him, and the rest will scatter. | I don't dare show my face, lest they recognize me, so you'll have to find out where they are.

Node.Caption: MS08SaadiaST20Final1: How am I supposed to get rid of them?

Cell.Text: [S] GS|No. There are too many people around. Come with me.
[S] G|I've told you, we can't talk out in the open. Come with me.
[S] So the Alik'r know where I am? What did they offer you? Gold? How many more of them are coming? | Tell me!

Node.Caption: MS08SaadiaST20Topic: Tell me what's going on.

Cell.Text: Then I need your help and there isn't anyone I can trust here in the city.

Node.Caption: MS08SaadiaST20Topic01: Relax, I'm not going to hurt you.

Cell.Text: I am not the person that the people of Whiterun think I am. My real name is Iman. I am a noble of House Suda in Hammerfell. | The men who are looking for me, the Alik'r, they are assassins in the employ of the Aldmeri Dominion. They wish to exchange my blood for gold. | I need you to root them out and drive them away before they find me and drag me back to Hammerfell for an execution.

Node.Caption: MS08SaadiaST20Topic01a: Maybe. What do you want?

Cell.Text: There will be. Of that, you can be assured.

Node.Caption: MS08SaadiaST20Topic01b: Perhaps. If there's money in it.

Cell.Text: You can't tell them! | Please, I need your help and there isn't anyone I can trust here in the city.

Node.Caption: MS08SaadiaST20Topic02: They just asked me to find you.

Cell.Text: Good. Wipe them out. So long as one of them is left alive, they will come for me!

Node.Caption: MS08SaadiaST75Topic: I know where the Alik'r are, and I have a way in.

Cell.Text: But where will I go? I can't keep running forever!

Node.Caption: MS08SaadiaST125FollowUp: They've found a way in. We need to get you out of here. (Lie)

Cell.Text: [S] After all this, I have to pick up and leave again? | If you really think this is the only way, I trust you. Let's not waste any time.

Node.Caption: MS08SaadiaST125Response1: There's a horse waiting at the stables. I'll make sure you're safe. (Lie)

Cell.Text: What? How? I thought they weren't allowed within the city!

Node.Caption: MS08SaadiaST125Topic: I was unable to defeat them all, and they're coming for you. (Lie)

Cell.Text: [S] At last. I can rest safely. You have done me a great service, warrior. I cannot thank you enough. | Take this reward. I managed to sneak some of my wealth out of Hammerfell when I left. It's the least I can do. | For now, I will maintain my ruse here. You are always welcome in the Bannered Mare.

Node.Caption: MS08SaadiaST160Topic: The Alik'r won't trouble you anymore.

Cell.Text: You think I'd be in hiding if this was something I trusted town guards to handle? | These men are ruthless. Cunning, deceitful... they'll pay off whoever they can. I can't trust anyone here in Whiterun. | Guards and Jarls can be bought. And the Alik'r are close; I'm running out of time, so I'm choosing to trust you.

Node.Caption: MS08SaadiaS25AlikrQuestionTopic: Why haven't you gone to the guards for help?

Cell.Text: I don't know for sure. I spoke out against the Aldmeri Dominion publicly; I suspect that's why these men were hired to hunt me down.

Node.Caption: MS08SaadiaStage25AlikrQuestion2Topic: Why are the Alik'r after you?

Cell.Text: [S] I heard one of them was just arrested trying to sneak into the city. If he's locked up in the jail, perhaps you can get it out of him. | Please, I know I'm asking you to do something difficult, maybe even dangerous. I just don't know who else I can trust.
I've run across these Alik'r before. I know where they're hiding.
[S] You've seen them? Then waste no time, head there at once! | The longer they're around, the more danger I'm in! Please, kill Kematu and end this nightmare for me!

Node.Caption: MS08SaadiaST20Final2: Any suggestions as to how I find them?

Cell.Text: I'm sorry, just... Just don't hurt me. I know you're not one of them, but you can't help them. You can't let them know I'm here. | Please, will you help me? There's no one here I can trust.

Node.Caption: MS08SaadiaST20Topic03: Put that down before you get hurt.

Cell.Text: You liar! | How could you do that to me!

Node.Caption: MS08SaadiaStage199BranchTopic: There, now you're safe.

Cell.Text: [S] G|You could have warned me you were baiting me into a trap. | But you're right. This should scatter the rest of them. I can go back to my life for now. | You have my thanks.

Node.Caption: MS08SaadiaStage199Response1: Relax. Kematu's dead, and now you're safe.

Cell.Text: [S] G|I can go back to my life for now. | And I have you to thank for it. I won't forget this.

Node.Caption: MS08SaadiaStage199Final

Cell.Text: A risky game to play, friend. | But now Kematu's gone, and the rest of his snakes should slither back to their desert.

Node.Caption: MS08SaadiaStage199Response2: I didn't want to risk you not coming.
